TY  - JOUR
AU  - Jia, Chunxin
AU  - Wang, Yaping
AU  - Xiong, Wei
T1  - Market Segmentation and Differential Reactions of Local and Foreign Investors to Analyst Recommendations
PY  - 2017
Y1  - 2017/09/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhx010
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 30
IS  - 9
SP  - 2972
EP  - 3008
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - This paper uses segmented dual-class shares of Chinese firms—A shares traded in mainland China by local investors and H shares traded in Hong Kong by foreign investors—to document a rich pattern in the differential reactions of local and foreign investors to analyst recommendations. This pattern reveals that social connections between analysts and investors affect investor reactions to analyst recommendations. Because of the investors’ differential reactions, analyst recommendations may exacerbate, rather than attenuate, the market segmentation between the two share classes.Received January 28, 2016; editorial decision October 23, 2016 by Editor Robin Greenwood.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhx010
ER  - 



